---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionLabel from '@/components/SectionLabel.astro';
import MarginNote from '@/components/MarginNote.astro';
import portrait from '@/assets/dennis.jpeg';

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Dennis Berger',
  url: 'https://dennisberger.me',
  jobTitle: 'Design Operations Leader',
  worksFor: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Taco Bell' },
  image: 'https://dennisberger.me/dennis.jpeg',
  address: { '@type': 'PostalAddress', addressLocality: 'Philadelphia', addressRegion: 'PA', addressCountry: 'US' },
  sameAs: ['https://linkedin.com/in/dennisberger'],
};
---

<Base
  title="About — Dennis Berger"
  description="Fifteen years leading design operations and UX strategy across Taco Bell, Comcast, Effectv, and GSK. How I think about systems, scale, and shipping."
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify(personSchema)} />
  <article class="about page">
    <SectionLabel>About</SectionLabel>
    <h1 class="about__title">Serious about outcomes.<br /><em>Not precious about process.</em></h1>
    <p class="about__lede">Design Operations and UX strategy leader based in Philadelphia.</p>

    <div class="about__body">
      <figure class="about__portrait">
        <Image
          src={portrait}
          alt="Dennis Berger"
          widths={[160, 220, 440]}
          sizes="(max-width: 720px) 160px, 220px"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
          quality={82}
        />
      </figure>
      <p>I'm a Design Operations and UX strategy leader based in Philadelphia, focused on building the systems and environments that help design teams ship work they're proud of.</p>
      <p>I started my career hands-on, writing my first line of HTML at 12 and spending years designing, building, and shipping digital products. That foundation shaped how I think about UX today: practical, user-centered, and grounded in the realities of delivery.</p>
      <MarginNote>The cool kids went to Geocities. I went to FrontPage and peeked at the code.</MarginNote>

      <h2>Career</h2>
      <ol class="about__career">
        <li>
          <time class="about__career-dates" datetime="2023">2023 —</time>
          <span class="about__career-role">Design Operations Lead</span>
          <span class="about__career-org">Taco Bell</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <time class="about__career-dates" datetime="2021/2023">2021 – 2023</time>
          <span class="about__career-role">Senior Program Manager</span>
          <span class="about__career-org">Comcast</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <time class="about__career-dates" datetime="2020/2021">2020 – 2021</time>
          <span class="about__career-role">Senior Product Designer</span>
          <span class="about__career-org">GSK</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <time class="about__career-dates" datetime="2017/2020">2017 – 2020</time>
          <span class="about__career-role">UX Engineer</span>
          <span class="about__career-org">Comcast Advertising (Effectv)</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <time class="about__career-dates" datetime="2010/2017">2010 – 2017</time>
          <span class="about__career-role">Founder &amp; UX Lead</span>
          <span class="about__career-org">TopClick</span>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>What I believe</h2>
      <ol class="about__beliefs">
        <li>
          <p><strong>DesignOps leadership asked to also set creative vision usually fails at both.</strong> They're different jobs, and the field keeps pretending they're one.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>A design system only exists to the degree that the people who don't work in design use it.</strong> Adoption is the deliverable. Everything else is Figma housekeeping.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Intake exists so the design org can make decisions at scale.</strong> A leader who bypasses it is signaling that decisions don't have to scale. The team reads that signal instantly.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Always building</h2>
      <p>I started as a founder. In 2010, I opened TopClick, a one-person UX consultancy that grew into seven years of end-to-end client work across strategy, design, development, and operations. I learned to ship consistently, balance competing constraints, and build trust on both sides of a contract. I also learned that the operational side of design was the part I kept getting pulled back to, long before anyone was calling it that.</p>
      <p>Eventually I took that wiring into larger organizations: Comcast Advertising, GSK, back to Comcast proper, now Taco Bell. The scope changed (regulated enterprise, multi-brand portfolios, audiences in the tens of millions) but the work was the same work. Operating models, research practices, tooling, ways of working that let teams scale without burning out or losing clarity.</p>
      <MarginNote>The scope scales. The playbook mostly doesn't.</MarginNote>
      <p>The agency was the first thing I built, but certainly not the last. <a href="https://ignyte.me" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ignyte</a> (self-hosted creator tools) and <a href="https://synoptro.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Synoptro</a> (DesignOps for people going it alone) are weekend experiments, with all that entails. They keep my text editor open, my skills fresh, and twelve-year-old me happy. Turns out he was right about the computer.</p>

      <h2>What I do now</h2>
      <p>Today, I lead Design Operations at Taco Bell, supporting a multidisciplinary UX team working across the mobile app, website, and in-store experiences. My work spans design systems, research operations, capacity planning, tooling and governance, and team enablement. The job is making design a reliable strategic partner to the business, and creating conditions where teams can focus on meaningful problems instead of fighting their tools.</p>

      <blockquote>Good operations should feel supportive, not restrictive. Teams do their best when they're trusted, resourced, and given room to experiment.</blockquote>

      <h2>How I work</h2>
      <p>Most of my work is one of three things: shaping an operating model, rolling out a design system, or helping a team through organizational change. Across all three, I care about being clear, pragmatic, and honest about what a team can actually sustain. Structure and flexibility aren't opposites; they reinforce each other when you get the balance right.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .about { padding-block: var(--space-section-hero) var(--space-section); max-width: var(--col-total); }
  /* Reserve a right gutter at desktop so MarginNote floats into it rather than
     sitting in the reading flow. Body content stays constrained to --col-main. */
  @media (min-width: 1080px) {
    .about__body { padding-right: calc(var(--col-gutter) + var(--col-gap)); }
    .about__body > p,
    .about__body > h2,
    .about__body > ol,
    .about__body > blockquote { max-width: var(--col-main); }
  }
  .about__title {
    font-size: var(--type-4xl);
    margin-block: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 20ch;
  }
  .about__title em { color: var(--color-fuchsia-deep); }
  .about__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-lg);
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-2xl);
  }
  .about__body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  .about__body p {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .about__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--type-2xl);
    margin-block: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-md);
  }
  .about__portrait {
    float: right;
    width: 220px;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) var(--space-xl);
    shape-outside: margin-box;
  }
  .about__portrait img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--color-paper-sunken);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .about__portrait {
      float: none;
      width: 160px;
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) 0;
    }
  }
  /* Career list shares its rhythm with `.about__beliefs` below:
     italic fuchsia display column left, stacked content column right,
     hairline rule between rows. */
  .about__career {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-block: var(--space-lg) var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .about__career li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 9.5rem 1fr;
    column-gap: var(--space-md);
    align-items: baseline;
    padding-block: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .about__career li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .about__career-dates {
    grid-column: 1;
    grid-row: 1 / span 2;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--type-xl);
    color: var(--color-fuchsia-deep);
    line-height: 1;
    padding-block-start: 0.1em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .about__career-role {
    grid-column: 2;
    grid-row: 1;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .about__career-org {
    grid-column: 2;
    grid-row: 2;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-block-start: var(--space-2xs);
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about__career li {
      grid-template-columns: 5rem 1fr;
    }
    .about__career-dates { font-size: var(--type-base); }
  }

  .about__beliefs {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: belief;
    padding: 0;
    margin-block: var(--space-xl) var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .about__beliefs li {
    counter-increment: belief;
    position: relative;
    padding-inline-start: calc(var(--space-xl) + var(--space-sm));
    padding-block: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .about__beliefs li::before {
    content: counter(belief, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    inset-inline-start: 0;
    inset-block-start: var(--space-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--type-xl);
    color: var(--color-fuchsia-deep);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .about__beliefs p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .about__beliefs strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .about__body blockquote {
    margin-block: var(--space-2xl);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-fuchsia);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-fuchsia);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--type-xl);
    background: var(--color-fuchsia-soft);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
</style>
